{{ja-kanjitab|ひのき|yomi=k|alt=桧:shinjitai,檜木}}
Originally a {{com+|ja||alt1=檜|tr1=hi|t1=[[Japanese cypress]]|pos1=see below|の|tr2=no|pos2=attributive particle|木|tr3=ki|t3=[[tree]]|nocap=1}}.<ref name="NKD">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten Concise|檜・檜木}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/>

The [[wood]] and [[bark]] was commonly used as [[tinder]], and the term was previously thought to be from {{com|ja|nocat=1|火|tr1=hi|t1=[[fire]]|の|tr2=no|pos2=attributive particle|木|tr3=ki|t3=tree}}. However, later research into {{w|Jōdai Tokushu Kanazukai|ancient kana usage}} in {{cog|ojp|-}} revealed that {{m|ja|檜}} had a reading of {{IPAfont|⟨pi<sub>1</sub>⟩}}, while {{m|ja|火}} was read as {{IPAfont|⟨pi<sub>2</sub>⟩}}, ruling out this derivation.<ref name="NKD"/>

